Develop a complete Parent Mobile Application for a Preschool Management System using the provided UI references as the base.

The system must follow a NIC-based parent validation model where parents are uniquely identified using their NIC number.

AUTHENTICATION:
- Implement Login and Sign Up as two separate flows.
- Sign Up validates NIC and registered email before allowing account creation.
- Login uses username and password.
- Email-based forgot password is mandatory.

PARENT CONTEXT:
- One parent can have multiple enrolled children.
- Automatically load all children linked to the parent NIC.
- Implement a global child switcher at the top of the app.

HOME:
- Display active child summary, attendance status, payment status, quick actions, recent updates, and upcoming events.

STUDENT PROFILE:
- Use a tab-based layout: Details, Progress, Attendance.
- Details must include full student bio, medical notes, emergency contact, and class info.
- Progress must show skill development using read-only animated progress bars and teacher notes.
- Attendance must show historical check-in/check-out data with summaries.

MEETINGS:
- Allow parents to request meetings with assigned teachers.
- Track meeting status and notify parents.

PAYMENTS:
- Allow parents to submit payments per child with month, amount, mandatory slip upload, and optional description.
- Show payment status as Pending or Paid based on admin approval.

UPDATES:
- Merge homework, alerts, and announcements into a unified feed with filters.

EVENTS:
- Implement a minimal event system focused on information, not social interaction.

SETTINGS:
- Allow parents to edit profile details except NIC.
- Include secure logout and password management.

DESIGN:
- Use a modern, clean, card-based UI.
- Apply Shadcn / Magic Pattern principles.
- Avoid bulky layouts.
- Ensure accessibility and usability.

SECURITY:
- Enforce strict role-based access control.
- Parent access must be read-only except for payments and meeting requests.

GOAL:
Deliver a secure, production-ready, modern parent application suitable for a real preschool environment in Sri Lanka.

